0California%2C%20she%20was%20laid%20off%20in%20June.%20The%20job%20was%20great%2C%20but%20the%20experience%20of%20getting%20axed%20shifted%20her%20priorities.%20Now%2C%20on%20the%20job%20hunt%2C%20she%20isn't%20messing%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20worrying%20about%20company%20culture%20or%20whether%20the%20job%20sounds%20exciting%2C%20the%20first%20thing%20Kaneshina%20looks%20for%20when%20job%20searching%20is%20the%20salary.%20%26quot%3BRight%20now%20there's%20this%20whole%20salary-transparency%20movement.%20So%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20roles%20I%20apply%20to%20I%20know%20about%20the%20pay%20right%20off%20the%20bat%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Once%20satisfied%20with%20the%20pay%20range%2C%20Kaneshina%20digs%20into%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20are%20they%20doing%20work%20she%20has%20experience%20with%3F%20Then%20she%20checks%20whether%20the%20opening%20provides%20room%20for%20growth%20%E2%80%94%20how%20long%20until%20she%20could%20get%20a%20promotion%3F%20For%20her%20to%20apply%2C%20all%20three%20factors%20have%20to%20line%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20young%20people%20are%20saying%20the%20same%20thing%3A%20Salary%20and%20career%20growth%20are%20the%20most%20important%20things%20about%20a%20job.%20And%20it%20could%20explain%20why%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20are%20so%20much%20more%20unsatisfied%20with%20their%20jobs%20than%20their%20older%20colleagues.%20Only%2044%25%20of%20workers%20under%2030%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F05%2F25%2Fyoung-workers-express-lower-levels-of-job-satisfaction-than-older-ones-but-most-are-content-with-their-job%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNearly%2520a%2520quarter%2520(23%2525)%2Cor%2520most%2520of%2520the%2520time.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPew%20Research%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20May%20that%20they%20were%20very%20satisfied%20with%20their%20job%2C%20compared%20with%2067%25%20of%20workers%2065%20and%20older.%20This%20is%20also%20a%20shift%20from%20when%20older%20generations%20were%20young%3A%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freason.com%2F1995%2F05%2F01%2Fheh-heh-work-is-cool%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E1995%20survey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20consulting%20firm%20Wyatt%20Co.%2C%20under-30%20Gen%20Xers%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D9Ht5RZpzPqw%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eworks%20sucks%2C%20I%20know%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20generation%20%E2%80%94%20were%20actually%20the%20most%20satisfied%20with%20their%20jobs%20than%20any%20other%20age%20group.%20Over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20the%20gap%20between%20young%20and%20old%20has%20widened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20has%20found%20that%20Gen%20Zers%20have%20different%20priorities%20from%20those%20of%20their%20boomer%20bosses.%20While%20pay%20and%20career%20progression%20are%20critical%20for%20the%20newest%20workers%2C%20older%20folks%20care%20more%20about%20whether%20the%20job%20itself%20is%20enjoyable.%20Age%20plays%20a%20role%20in%20explaining%20the%20gap%2C%20but%20Gen%20Z%20is%20also%20entering%20the%20workforce%20at%20a%20unique%20time.%20After%20witnessing%20millennials%20being%20sold%20on%20the%20false%20promise%20that%20landing%20a%20job%20and%20clocking%20in%20the%20hours%20would%20lead%20to%20a%20steady%20climb%20up%20the%20career%20ladder%20and%20pay%20scale%2C%20and%20all%20the%20chaos%20that%20wrought%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20much%20less%20apt%20to%20entrust%20their%20futures%20to%20their%20employers.%20As%20Business%20Insider%20correspondent%20Aki%20Ito%20wrote%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eloyalty%20contract%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20employers%20and%20employees%20is%20broken.%20Now%2C%20during%20a%20time%20of%20high%20inflation%20and%20massive%20student-loan%20debt%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20taking%20their%20futures%20into%20their%20own%20hands%20by%20prioritizing%20high%20pay%20and%20progression%20above%20all%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20past%2C%20people%20were%20provided%20with%20really%20great%20jobs%2C%20pensions%2C%20and%20careers%20that%20they%20could%20grow%20at%20a%20company%20for%2020%20years.%20That's%20not%20how%20it%20is%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Kaneshina%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BI've%20just%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20what%20adulthood%20is%20actually%20like.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPriorities%20change%20over%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20has%20remained%20true%20across%20generations%3A%20What%20we%20value%20about%20our%20work%20changes%20over%20time%2C%20Julia%20Kensbock%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20organization%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Bremen%20in%20Germany%2C%20told%20me.%20She%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1002%2Fhrm.21981%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epaper%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202019%20that%20found%20pay%20was%20especially%20important%20for%20young%20people's%20job%20satisfaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20are%20young%2C%20we%20worry%20more%20about%20our%20long-term%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20As%20we%20get%20older%2C%20we%20tend%20to%20shift%20our%20focus%20toward%20short-term%20goals%20that%20help%20us%20maintain%20positive%20feelings%20and%20mental%20well-being.%20%26quot%3BWe%20also%20want%20to%20contribute%20something%20back%20to%20society%20or%20to%20our%20organizations%20that%20we%20work%20at%2C%26quot%3B%20Kensbock%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Bain%20%26amp%3B%20Co.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bain.com%2Finsights%2Fbetter-with-age-the-rising-importance-of-older-workers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20July%20found%20something%20similar.%20Workers%20over%2062%20said%20that%20interesting%20work%20was%20their%20top%20priority%20on%20the%20job%2C%20but%20workers%20in%20the%2018-to-25%20age%20bracket%20said%20they%20prioritized%20good%20compensation%2C%20followed%20by%20learning%20and%20growth.%20While%20everyone%20says%20that%20a%20good%20salary%20is%20important%2C%20its%20significance%20tends%20to%20decrease%20as%20people%20get%20older.%20Kensbock's%20research%20also%20found%20that%20younger%20employees'%20job%20satisfaction%20was%20primarily%20linked%20to%20output.%20If%20they%20sense%20they%20have%20been%20underrewarded%2C%20or%20their%20efforts%20haven't%20translated%20to%20satisfying%20financial%20returns%2C%20they%20feel%20worse%20about%20their%20job.%20On%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20senior%20workers'%20job%20satisfaction%20is%20primarily%20linked%20to%20input%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they%20contribute%20meaningfully%20to%20a%20task%2C%20they're%20more%20satisfied%20with%20their%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKensbrock%20told%20me%20that%20this%20phenomenon%20was%20largely%20due%20to%20age%20%E2%80%94%20not%20generation.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20tendency%20of%20mixing%20up%20these%20generation%20effects%20with%20the%20age%20effects.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20she%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20societal%20trends%20on%20a%20broader%20basis%20that%20affect%20how%20we%20as%20a%20society%20perceive%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20past%20few%20years%20certainly%20have%20seen%20a%20seismic%20shift%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20which%20has%20left%20Gen%20Zers%20reeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20what's%20new%20with%20Gen%20Z%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20new%20workers%20were%20told%20that%20if%20they%20stuck%20with%20one%20company%2C%20that%20company%20would%20reward%20them.%20The%20way%20to%20climb%20the%20ranks%20and%20get%20that%20coveted%20paycheck%20was%20to%20put%20your%20head%20down%20and%20work%20for%20it.%20But%20today%2C%20that%20no%20longer%20holds%20true.%20Over%20the%20past%20several%20years%2C%20remote%20work%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BGreat%20Resignation%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20flood%20of%20layoffs%20have%20shifted%20how%20people%20see%20their%20jobs.%20Employers%20demonstrated%20their%20infidelity%20to%20their%20staff%20by%20paying%20loyal%20workers%2C%20on%20average%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-resignation-pay-gap-new-hires-earning-more-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E7%25%20less%20than%20new%20hires%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlantafed.org%2Fchcs%2Fwage-growth-tracker%3Fpanel%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esalaries%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20largely%20the%20same%20between%20new%20and%20longtime%20employees.%20None%20of%20this%20was%20lost%20on%20those%20just%20entering%20the%20workforce.%20In%202021%2C%20junior%20workers%20rated%20their%20companies%202.4%25%20worse%20than%20their%20senior%20colleagues%20did%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reveliolabs.com%2Fnews%2Fsocial%2Fa-tale-of-two-cultures-in-one-company%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERevelio%20Labs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20in%20an%20analysis%20of%20employer%20reviews%20on%20sites%20like%20Glassdoor.%20By%20November%2C%20that%20gap%20had%20increased%20to%204%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20there's%20almost%20this%20distrust%20in%20our%20employers%2C%26quot%3B%20Kaneshina%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20going%20to%20advocate%20for%20ourselves%20more%20because%20we%20really%20don't%20know%20how%20our%20employers%20are%20going%20to%20help%20us%20in%20the%20long%20run.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20the%20promise%20of%20high%20returns%20for%20their%20loyalty%2C%20Gen%20Z%20has%20learned%20to%20follow%20the%20money.%20In%20CFA%20Institute's%202021%20survey%20of%20more%20than%2015%2C000%20recent%20college%20graduates%2C%2045%25%20of%2018-%20to%2025-year-olds%20said%20that%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20salary%26quot%3B%20was%20the%20most%20important%20criterion%20for%20a%20job.%20In%20its%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfainstitute.org%2F-%2Fmedia%2Fdocuments%2Fsurvey%2FCFA-Institute-Global-Graduate-Outlook-Survey-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esurvey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20jumped%20to%2062%25.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelasallenetwork.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FClass-of-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esurvey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20graduating%20college%20seniors%20conducted%20last%20year%20by%20the%20staffing%20firm%20LaSalle%20Network%2C%2054%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20who%20were%20just%20entering%20the%20workforce%20said%20they%20expected%20to%20secure%20their%20first%20promotion%20within%20one%20year%20on%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20all%20generations%20had%20to%20start%20somewhere%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20face%20record-high%20costs%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-outlook-home-sales-affordable-inventory-demographics-population-property-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehousing%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-tuition-costs-too-much-make-degrees-matter-less-jobs-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecollege%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20basics%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-food-prices-inflation-gas-costs-groceries-restaurants-americans-economy-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efood%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20many%20people%2C%20getting%20a%20good%20salary%20is%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20being%20able%20to%20cover%20costs.%20In%20EY's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ey.com%2Fen_us%2Fconsulting%2Fgenerational-dynamics%2F2023-gen-z-study%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2023%20Gen%20Z%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20survey%2C%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20said%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20worried%20about%20not%20having%20enough%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20about%20the%20money%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20being%20greedy%2C%26quot%3B%20Corey%20Seemiller%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20organizational%20leadership%20at%20Wright%20State%20University%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20the%20money%20and%20being%20able%20to%20pay%20for%20living%20expenses%2C%20which%20is%20reasonable.%20The%20dollar%20went%20a%20lot%20further%20when%20baby%20boomers%20were%20entering%20the%20workforce.%20It%20doesn't%20go%20as%20far%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20is%20also%20keenly%20aware%20of%20the%20long-term%20financial%20challenges%20they%20face%2C%20with%20many%20targeting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-125000-need-feel-theyve-made-it-study-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esix-figure%20salaries%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20early%20in%20their%20careers%20to%20save%20up%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-will-happen-baby-boomer-homes-die-millennials-gen-z-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebuying%20a%20home%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-most-financially-savvy-generation-retirement-saving-investing-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eretirement%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cigna.com.hk%2Fiwov-resources%2Fdocs%2FCigna-360-Global-Well-being-Survey.PDF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECigna%20survey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%2012%2C000%20global%20workers%2C%2039%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20identified%20financial%20insecurity%20as%20their%20top%20stressor%2C%20the%20highest%20of%20any%20generation.%20%26quot%3BThey%20know%20that%2C%20later%20on%2C%20choosing%20a%20certain%20career%20path%20will%20have%20economic%20impacts%20that%20the%20rest%20of%20us%20didn't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20Seemiller%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20generation%20also%20has%20unprecedented%20access%20to%20information%20about%20the%20working%20world.%20Before%20the%20internet%2C%20it%20took%20time%20for%20new%20workers%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20ins%20and%20outs%20of%20their%20respective%20fields%20%E2%80%94%20the%20only%20option%20was%20to%20learn%20on%20the%20job.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpassive-income-tiktok-youtube-rise-of-side-hustle-hucksters-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einfluencers%3C%2Fu%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3E%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cu%3Eon%20TikTok%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20YouTube%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-tiktok-workers-employees-oversharing-about-jobs-work-side-hustle-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20gained%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20followers%20by%20sharing%20tips%20on%20how%20to%20ace%20interviews%2C%20negotiate%20salaries%2C%20and%20handle%20performance%20reviews.%20And%20by%20watching%20people%20on%20the%20internet%20advancing%20through%20their%20careers%20quickly%2C%20young%20people%20gain%20the%20confidence%20to%20pursue%20that%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20horizon%20and%20the%20possibilities%20have%20changed%2C%20making%20it%20transparent%20and%20visible%20what%20people%20can%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Felizitas%20Lichtenberg%2C%20the%20global%20head%20of%20diversity%20and%20inclusion%20at%20the%20fintech%20company%20SumUp%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20of%20social%20media%20and%20the%20pressure%20that%20teenagers%20have%20nowadays%2C%20it's%20so%20outward-facing%20that%20this%20is%20also%20impacting%20what%20people%20are%20looking%20for%20in%20terms%20of%20growth%20opportunities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeemiller%20said%20Gen%20Z's%20desire%20to%20be%20promot