BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENato%20slammed%2C%20Maga%20boosted%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20predictably%20the%20Russia%20president%20blamed%20what%20he%20identified%20as%20Nato%20expansionism%20and%20threats%20to%20his%20country%E2%80%99s%20security.%20He%20recounted%20how%20he%20had%20offered%20a%20hand%20of%20friendship%20to%20the%20US%3A%20%E2%80%9CPlease%20don%E2%80%99t%20%5Bexpand%20Nato%20eastward%5D.%20We%20are%20as%20bourgeois%20now%20as%20you%20are.%20We%20are%20a%20market%20economy%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20Communist%20party%20power.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20negotiate.%E2%80%9D%20But%20his%20overtures%20were%20spurned%20by%20the%20US%20elites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%20predictably%2C%20both%20interviewer%20and%20interviewee%20took%20the%20opportunity%20to%20boost%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20his%20Make%20America%20Great%20Again%20(Maga)%20voter%20base.%20Trump%20has%20already%20said%20he%20would%20end%20US%20military%20aid%20to%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20quickly%E2%80%9D%20by%20withdrawing%20US%20aid%2C%20something%20that%20Putin%20stressed%20in%20the%20interview%3A%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20really%20want%20to%20stop%20fighting%2C%20you%20need%20to%20stop%20supplying%20weapons.%20It%20will%20be%20over%20within%20a%20few%20weeks.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Putin%20chose%20not%20to%20dwell%20at%20length%20on%20what%20a%20Trump%20presidency%20could%20do%20for%20him.%20Instead%20he%20took%20a%20shot%20at%20US%20policy%20on%20Ukraine%20as%20a%20distraction%20from%20America%E2%80%99s%20domestic%20woes%2C%20zeroing%20in%20on%20what%20is%20a%20sore%20point%20for%20many%20swing%20voters%20%E2%80%93%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20have%20issues%20on%20the%20border%2C%20issues%20with%20migration%2C%20issues%20with%20the%20national%20debt%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20Carlson.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20have%20nothing%20better%20to%20do%2C%20so%20you%20should%20fight%20in%20Ukraine%3F%20Wouldn%E2%80%99t%20it%20be%20better%20to%20negotiate%20with%20Russia%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20president%20floated%20the%20idea%20that%20US%20foreign%20policy%20decisions%20had%20been%20captured%20by%20what%20he%20called%20%E2%80%9Celites%E2%80%99%20mindsets%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20while%20Trump%20may%20well%20change%20US%20policy%20towards%20Russia%2C%20it%20would%20only%20happen%20if%20the%20%E2%80%9Celites%20change%E2%80%9D%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECarlson%20filled%20in%20the%20gap%2C%20echoing%20another%20of%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20key%20themes%20%E2%80%93%20the%20power%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdeep%20state%E2%80%9D%3A%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20twice%20you%E2%80%99ve%20described%20US%20presidents%20making%20decisions%20and%20then%20being%20undercut%20by%20their%20agency%20heads.%20So%2C%20it%20sounds%20like%20you%E2%80%99re%20describing%20a%20system%20that%20is%20not%20run%20by%20the%20people%20who%20are%20elected%2C%20in%20your%20telling.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETalking%20to%20an%20America%20in%20turmoil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20controversial%20interview%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2023%2F34%2Fspecial-articles%2Fpoly-crisis-or-organic-crisis.html%5C%22%3Egreat%20turmoil%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20the%20US%20and%20internationally.%20Trump%20%E2%80%93%20for%20whom%20Carlson%20campaigned%20in%20the%202020%20election%20campaign%20%E2%80%93%20faces%20a%20string%20of%20court%20cases%2C%20including%20some%20that%20could%20%E2%80%93%20if%20he%E2%80%99s%20convicted%20%E2%80%93%20see%20him%20imprisoned%20before%20the%20November%202024%20presidential%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2024%2Ffeb%2F07%2Fus-supreme-court-trump-case-eligible-for-2024-run%5C%22%3Ealso%20rule%20on%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20Trump%20should%20be%20removed%20from%20the%20ballot%20altogether%20due%20to%20charges%20of%20insurrectionary%20conduct%20on%20January%206%202021.%20Congress%20also%20remains%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2023%2Fdec%2F07%2Fbiden-ukraine-funding-bill-mexico-border%5C%22%3Eat%20loggerheads%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20providing%20further%20financial%20support%20to%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20he%20is%20likely%20to%20win%20the%20Republican%20presidential%20nomination%2C%20Trump%20faces%20a%20primary%20challenge%20from%20Nikki%20Haley%2C%20who%20now%20represents%20an%20important%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.1080%2F14747731.2021.1991660%5C%22%3Efocal%20point%20of%20opposition%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Trump%20the%20personality%20rather%20than%20to%20Trumpism%20the%20idea.%20Haley%2C%20former%20governor%20of%20South%20Carolina%20and%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20is%20also%20a%20champion%20of%20US%20support%20for%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20resistance%20to%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20military%20might%20%E2%80%93%20as%20is%20Joe%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ftrumps-nato-remarks-met-with-biden-eu-backlash%5C%22%3ETrump%E2%80%99s%20NATO%20Remarks%20Met%20With%20Biden%2C%20EU%20Backlash%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20%E2%80%93%20and%20Trump%2C%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20fact%20%E2%80%93%20campaigned%20on%20the%20idea%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpolitics%2F2020%2F12%2F09%2Fbiden-wars-terrorism-iraq-afhganistan-syria%2F%5C%22%3Eending%20America%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cforever%20wars%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Yet%20the%20US%20is%20now%20embroiled%20in%20a%20series%20of%20conflicts%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fatul-bharadwaj-and-inderjeet-parmar%5C%22%3Eglobal%20arc%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Ukraine%2C%20through%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20all%20the%20way%20to%20simmering%20tensions%20over%20Taiwan.%20A