led%20to%20catch%20any%20rot%20that%20has%20set%20in.%20%E2%80%9CEven%20one%20seed%20with%20fungus%20can%20affect%20the%20whole%20batch%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20warns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStep%203%3A%20Divide%20the%20batch%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESorting%20through%20the%20seeds%20leaves%20you%20with%20the%20good%20ones%20and%20the%20bad.%20You%20discard%20the%20bad%20ones%20and%20proceed%20with%20silvering%20the%20good%20ones.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20step%2C%20the%20tail-like%20portion%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20seed%20is%20cut%20off%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Vaibhav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F270107%2Fterrace-gardening-tips-how-to-grow-vegetables-at-home%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethese%20seeds%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20then%20divided%20into%20two%20batches.%20%E2%80%9COne%20batch%20is%20put%20into%20soil%20trays%20and%20the%20other%20in%20wooden%20trays%20on%20slotted%20angle%20racks.%20Both%20the%20setups%20are%20kept%20in%20a%20room%20where%20the%20temperature%20is%20stringently%20controlled.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-2-1707479222.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20saffron%20threads%20are%20the%20stigma%20of%20the%20flower%20that%20are%20harvested%20and%20dried%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-2-1707479222.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-2-1707479222-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-2-1707479222-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-2-1707479222-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-2-1707479222-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341328%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20saffron%20threads%20are%20the%20stigma%20of%20the%20flower%20that%20are%20harvested%20and%20dried%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Vaibhav%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-3-1707479405.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Taking%20out%20the%20stigmas%20from%20the%20flower%20is%20a%20manual%20time-consuming%20process%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-3-1707479405.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-3-1707479405-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-3-1707479405-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-3-1707479405-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fsaffron-3-1707479405-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341329%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETaking%20out%20the%20stigmas%20from%20the%20flower%20is%20a%20manual%20time-consuming%20process%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Vaibhav%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aim%20is%20to%20mimic%20the%20climes%20of%20the%20Valley%2C%20as%20the%20seeds%20only%20flower%20at%20a%20specific%20temperature.%20Elaborating%20on%20how%20they%20managed%20to%20achieve%20this%2C%20Vaibhav%20says%20%E2%80%9CThe%20temperature%20in%20the%20room%20has%20to%20be%20decreased%20gradually%20just%20as%20if%20winter%20is%20coming%20to%20Kashmir.%20We%E2%80%99re%20essentially%20trying%20to%20make%20the%20seeds%20feel%20at%20home.%20So%2C%20we%20start%20at%2025%20degrees%20Celsius%20and%20gradually%20drop%20the%20temperature%20to%20five%20degrees%20through%20the%20next%20four%20months%20until%20harvest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStep%204%3A%20Pluck%20the%20flowers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20purple%20bloom%20conveys%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F276908%2Fdehradun-gardener-flower-plants-how-to-garden-youtube%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20harvest%20is%20ready%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Each%20flower%20comprises%20petals%2C%20the%20stamen%20and%20the%20stigma.%20%E2%80%9CEach%20of%20these%20parts%20has%20a%20different%20use.%20The%20petals%20are%20used%20in%20the%20cosmetic%20industry%2C%20the%20yellow%20stamen%20is%20used%20in%20the%20textile%20industry%20for%20dyeing%2C%20and%20the%20stigma%20is%20the%20red%20saffron.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStep%205%3A%20Place%20the%20seeds%20back%20into%20the%20soil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20flowers%20have%20been%20plucked%20out%2C%20all%20the%20seeds%20are%20placed%20back%20into%20the%20soil%20so%20they%20can%20flower%20again%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Vaibhav%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20cycle%20that%20began%20on%2015%20August%20was%20completed%20on%201%20November%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEnsure%20that%20you%20water%20the%20seeds%20every%207%20to%2010%20days%2C%20and%20not%20exceed%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20informs.%20Once%20it%E2%80%99s%20August%2C%20the%20flowers%20will%20be%20harvested%20again.%20%E2%80%9CThus%2C%20you%20see%2C%20each%20bulb%20has%20a%20lifetime%20of%20a%20decade%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F17686%2F5-secrets-to-the-most-amazing-terrace-garden-fro